Good! So `ExtensionMessage` is defined as:
```typescript
{
  type: string;
  payload?: unknown;
}
```

So `{ type: "PONG" }` is a valid `ExtensionMessage`. But the issue is that `sendResponse` in the `chrome.runtime.onMessage` callback expects a `CommandResponseMessage`, not any `ExtensionMessage`.

Let me check `CommandResponseMessageSchema`:

